ve as much power as they do because they spread so many lies and so much fear. The greatest way to fight fear is with knowledge.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/CoYAeWA</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SatanicOtaku]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The Crowd Goes Silent</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/VWxW8Vp</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0F9GsrP.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/VWxW8Vp</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Devi8tor]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>might make an Amazon OC (repost, coz im dumb)</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/nUQSrjB</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Qc8fLwe.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>muscles.png</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/nUQSrjB</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[m4rjinn]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>F*** racism</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/AEnvoIL</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/XAj07Yr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/B9HYsAZ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0kyFlZd.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/XBjvoC3.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Correction: the guy was John Keglovics, Jackie's boyfriend NOT her ex-husband Carl Harford. Thanks GraemeDynard.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/AEnvoIL</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Yermamma]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I'm honestly not sure how to handle this.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/NRYAKp1</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6Fpgwqn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I've made it a personal policy to ignore drama and help where I can. My brother isn't the greatest person, but he's trying. Problem is, he's got a poor taste in company, and it's not uncommon for him to bring his girlfriend around from time to time. Today one of their arguments became really loud...</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hylAowT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I became involved, separated the two, and kept things as close to peaceful as possible. It was decided then that she wouldn't be coming back after this. Having some experience in security work, I recognized that the two would just provoke eachother, but lordy lordry, the GF kept trying to yell all manners of insults and criticisms in an attempt to rile up my brother.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pwcuKhA.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I remained courteous, ensured that the GF had time enough to gather her things. What bothered me however was that somewhere between her loud grievances, she mentioned calling someone to "make sure he gets what he's got coming to him" and that it would probably be her father or uncle. I was dismissive of it at first, but noted it.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eWuYZtW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The more distance you can get between two parties with hostile attitudes, the better. She wanted to call for a ride home, and I wanted as much of a buffer zone as I could create. The problem came up when she began telling me directly that she'd call someone, and that "He'd get what's coming to him, and you for enabling him."</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/O957FyD.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>She called someone else, started describing in detail her opinions of myself and my brother, suggested I was part of the problem, and then stepped out of earshot. I used to work security for a bit, so I decided that maybe I should listen to my gut and quietly text the police about the safety concern.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/argtY1m.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The police arrived, two vehicles. They were pretty quick to hear out my concerns.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Y3YfQtt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I was immediately thankful for the police presence when these strangers pulled up, and exited their vehicle. Not one or two, but THREE people exited the vehicle and approached quickly. The police officer interviewing the GF instructed all three to immediately return to their vehicle.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sbbz6Pz.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I've seen police work quite a bit in my old job. Usually when someone starts making threats, it's easy to trespass them and ensure they never come back. Three people pulling up and charging in the direction of the police? Icing on the cake.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mkm1AZs.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Things took a pretty quick turn-around after the GF talked with the police. The responding officers decided that it was a domestic abuse incident, and instead cuffed my brother then and there. Alright, that's something that can be addressed in court.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/J3yYfK1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Professionalism and courtesy are key, but I did notice that the police were focusing unusually on only one issue, while neglecting to mention anything about the original problem. When I asked them if they'd at least gathered any information, in case the group returned, all three said no. 

I was dumbfounded.

Okay, there's some requirements to request an ID, but that doesn't stop the common sense practice of getting a license plate, or any sort of information that could be referenced if the trio or GF returned at a later time. Instead they insisted that "Nothing happened".</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vRVRvpU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I pointed out the unusual logic they were employing, specifically that they themselves witnessed a vehicle pull up with three occupants that were not hesitant to approach with haste. Their response was that the group came to pick her up, as she'd called for a ride home.

It wasn't hard to appreciate the strangeness of it. A person threatens to call someone and have said someone make sure my brother "gets what he has coming", and then three people show up when one could have easily come to get her, and then ALL THREE make a hasty advance until they recognize the presence of law enforcement...

...but no, nothing suspicious there, apparently.

I think what made it sting a little more was that the officer suggested the additional numbers were needed because "they were concerned". This was coming from a police officer. A police officer. The a member of the law enforcement agency I called because I was concerned.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rrlSHAQ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This one really got me. While they were interviewing her, she apparently told them she was a resident of the property. No keys, not here for any extended time, but the police took her at her word. Sucks for me, because they refused to budge on this even a little.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ngNV8vf.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This hurt. In security work, we don't have room for questions like this to go unanswered. Either we answer it with facts, or our input is treated as little more than a poorly timed fart during a hurricane.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/npluEok.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VuFcJkt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/oL7zVAZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>TLDR: Called the police to be present if anyone showed up to be violent, police stop a group that showed up to be violent, then arrested my brother and proceeded to let the group go without identifying any of them in any fashion that would allow a followup if they show up to be violent again.

I don't care about upvotes. I just want help. I'm concerned for my safety, and the police only made things worse without actually addressing the problem.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/NRYAKp1</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[WriteorWrong]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>They have no shame nor any ability to lead</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/F8DUkts</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ab9VunV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/F8DUkts</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Lanhdanan]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Politely and Respectfully.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/qCyuOvk</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xRqKhqZ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Don't forget, YSTFU  and YSYFBFM</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/qCyuOvk</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ufoara]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Dump, pox edition</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Lt4oj5t</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3SJ19wR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>After two years of making good choices</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LjPivFS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Masking, distancing,  avoiding crowded places</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/XJsSlmw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The pox has hit my house... the kids missed the last fun days of school</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xyMFYWU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Spouse and I had to take days off work.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mQEhzEy.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We're all vaccinated and boosted as appropriate</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/uNw1Q2D.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>But it's still hitting hard.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/upFDWZP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Thankfully the youngest is starting to perk up, so that means it must come to an end.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GKxlehn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>All of that anxiety any fear had dimmed until the positive tests came back.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/31Tbv41.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I felt the original fear again, from the early days,  what if one of us has a really bad case?</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/durSglZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>All I can do is keep everyone hydrated, resting, taking vitamins.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3Txr0Uo.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We're re-watching Stranger Things before the new season drops. It's a good distraction from the coughing.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7Dd2efS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We have friends and family, food and supplies, and flexible virtual jobs.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Va4FUop.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Considering all of that I guess getting the pox now is best case scenario, rather than in the beginning with no vaccine and hospitals full.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5TuM3s6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We'll stay home and quietly quarantine, like so many other families.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/568X6Kc.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I just kind of wanted to call into the void a bit.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/OPMZA3D.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Hopefully this means we'll be extra immune for the next few months.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dvqdJTW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LPGjcVR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7U1Nffb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HZ2HVRW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5S6Nweb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jp2uqMB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2tzWI0F.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/opzugOG.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/O1EPICb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qF0FmYb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rcc4Fhj.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dGBCoqR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GiAOpXj.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The dog is, of 